    "title": {
      "rendered": "How Twitter Donations Work: What Your Nonprofit Needs to Know"
    },
    "content": {
      "rendered": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/How-Twitter-Donations-Work-Square.jpg\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-20596\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/How-Twitter-Donations-Work-Square-300x300.jpg?resize=300%2C300\" alt=\"Web\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/How-Twitter-Donations-Work-Square.jpg?resize=300%2C300&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/How-Twitter-Donations-Work-Square.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/How-Twitter-Donations-Work-Square.jpg?resize=768%2C768&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/How-Twitter-Donations-Work-Square.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/How-Twitter-Donations-Work-Square.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/How-Twitter-Donations-Work-Square.jpg?w=800&amp;ssl=1 800w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" /></a>Twitter is experimenting with allowing <em>certain</em> nonprofits to accept donations directly through tweets. Like how only a select few nonprofits had access to Facebook&#8217;s early launch of their <strong><a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/07/10/what-your-nonprofit-needs-to-know-about-facebooks-new-fundraising-tools/\">Facebook Fundraising Tools</a></strong>, only a select few nonprofits currently have access to <strong><a href=\"https://support.twitter.com/articles/20174575\" target=\"_blank\">Twitter Donations</a>. </strong>It is unclear if Twitter has plans to provide access to more nonprofits in the near future, but doing so would be a smart move. It&#8217;s becoming increasingly clear that\u00a0digital payments will be central to the social network experience in 2017 and thereafter.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">For Twitter to expand the service to all nonprofits in the United States they would have partner with a database like <strong><a href=\"https://www.guidestar.org/Home.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">GuideStar USA</a></strong> (to easily verify a nonprofit&#8217;s legal status) and a donation processing service, such as <strong><a href=\"http://www.networkforgood.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Network for Good</a></strong>. With charitable giving in the United States at <strong><a href=\"https://givingusa.org/giving-usa-2016/\" target=\"_blank\">a record high of $373.25 billion</a></strong> given annually and a growing percentage of that amount being given online, it&#8217;s time for Twitter<em> (and Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn, and Snapchat) </em>to take the financial power of the philanthropic sector more seriously.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Expanding Twitter Donations\u00a0internationally is more challenging because an international database of verified nonprofits doesn&#8217;t exist and international banking transfers are more costly and complicated, however, <strong><a href=\"https://www.globalgiving.org/\" target=\"_blank\">GlobalGiving</a></strong> would be a good partner for expanding internationally. Twitter (<em>and Facebook, Instagram, LinkedIn, and Snapchat) </em>could also consider expanding\u00a0the donation service to nonprofits, charities and NGOs that use the <a href=\"https://www.name.com/domains/tech4good\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>.NGO and .ONG domains for the website and email communications</strong></a> since only legally verified nonprofits, charities, and NGOs (and ONGs) can use the new domains. The domains themselves serve as verification and that&#8217;s not a very difficult piece of code to write.\u00a0<em>Hint, hint.\u00a0</em></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">1) Donors can now give directly through Twitter. See <a href=\"https://twitter.com/Water/status/792350306134700032\" target=\"_blank\">@Water</a>, for example.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Water/status/792350306134700032\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-20604 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-11.png?resize=600%2C464\" alt=\"twitter-donation-11\" width=\"600\" height=\"464\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-11.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-11.png?resize=300%2C232&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">2)\u00a0For the first donation, donors must enter their credit card information.<a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-2.png\"><br />\n</a></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Water/status/792350306134700032\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20575\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-2-1.png?resize=500%2C555\" alt=\"twitter-donation-2\" width=\"500\" height=\"555\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-2-1.png?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-2-1.png?resize=270%2C300&amp;ssl=1 270w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></a></p>\n<h1>3)\u00a0Every donation thereafter to any participating nonprofit can be made in two taps/clicks using their saved credit card information.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Water/status/792350306134700032\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20577\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twit-Donations-22.jpg?resize=500%2C435\" alt=\"twit-donations-22\" width=\"500\" height=\"435\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twit-Donations-22.jpg?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twit-Donations-22.jpg?resize=300%2C261&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong>4) After giving, donors can easily tweet their donation.</strong></h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Water/status/792350306134700032\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20580\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-3.jpg?resize=500%2C497\" alt=\"twitter-donation-3\" width=\"500\" height=\"497\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-3.jpg?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-3.jpg?resize=150%2C150&amp;ssl=1 150w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-3.jpg?resize=300%2C298&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-3.jpg?resize=200%2C200&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-3.jpg?resize=75%2C75&amp;ssl=1 75w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-66.png\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-20608 aligncenter\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-66.png?resize=500%2C363\" alt=\"twitter-donation-66\" width=\"500\" height=\"363\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-66.png?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-66.png?resize=300%2C218&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">5) Donors can view their donation history under Settings &gt; Order history.</h1>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Water/status/792350306134700032\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20612\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-55.png?resize=600%2C239\" alt=\"twitter-donation-55\" width=\"600\" height=\"239\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-55.png?w=600&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-55.png?resize=300%2C120&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></a></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Water/status/792350306134700032\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-20585\" style=\"border: 1px solid black;\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-6.png?resize=500%2C363\" alt=\"twitter-donation-6\" width=\"500\" height=\"363\" srcset=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-6.png?w=500&amp;ssl=1 500w, https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/Twitter-Donation-6.png?resize=300%2C218&amp;ssl=1 300w\" sizes=\"auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px\" /></a></p>\n<h1 style=\"text-align: left;\">6) Nonprofits are provided the donor&#8217;s email address for a follow-up thank you email and email engagement.</h1>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://twitter.com/Water/status/792350306134700032\" target=\"_blank\">Water.org</a></strong> has yet to send a thank you, but the donation was only made two days ago, so it is likely coming. That said, I have made <a href=\"http://www.nptechforgood.com/2016/07/10/what-your-nonprofit-needs-to-know-about-facebooks-new-fundraising-tools/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>16 donations to nonprofits via Facebook</strong></a> this year and not one of them has sent a thank you follow-up email. In addition,\u00a0I have also made numerous donations via <strong><a href=\"https://support.google.com/youtube/answer/6318560?hl=en\" target=\"_blank\">YouTube Donation Cards</a></strong> and again, haven&#8217;t received any kind of acknowledgement. Nonprofits, you need to get much better at thanking donors who give directly through social networks \u2013 <em>and fast.</em></p>\n<hr />\n<h2 style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong style=\"font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 17px;\"><span style=\"color: #000000;\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 18px; font-weight: bold;\"><em>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</em></span></span></strong></h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\"><img data-recalc-dims=\"1\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-full wp-image-16887 alignleft\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/www.nptechforgood.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/mobile-for-good-with-ribbon.jpg?resize=99%2C150\" alt=\"mobile for good with ribbon\" width=\"99\" height=\"150\" /></a>Based on more than 20 years of experience and 25,000+ hours spent utilizing mobile and social media, <a href=\"http://www.amazon.com/Mobile-Good-How--Fundraising-Nonprofits/dp/0071825460\" target=\"_blank\"><em><strong>Mobile for Good: A How-To Fundraising Guide for Nonprofits</strong></em></a> is a comprehensive 256-page book packed with more than 500 best practices. Written on the premise that all communications and fundraising are now mobile and social, Mobile for Good is a step-by-step how-to guide for writing, implementing, and maintaining a mobile and social fundraising strategy for your nonprofit.</p>\n",
